title: Ground News - Two Lawrenceville men dead following crash into trees
text:
Summary by Ground News Two young men have died following a single vehicle crash in Lawrence County. The driver of a Chevrolet 2500 ran off the road at a curve through an embankment and struck two trees . Police identified the driver as Mason R. Deisher, 26, while the passenger was identified as Wade J. Lackey, 22, both of Lawrenceville. Share menu More

mywabashvalley.com Center High Factuality Two Lawrenceville men dead following crash into trees LAWRENCE COUNTY, Ill. (WTWO/WAWV) — Two young men have died following a single vehicle crash in Lawrence County. According to Illinois State Police, the crash occurred at approximately 2:15 a.m. on December 23 along Illinois Route 33 south of Elm Street. Investigating troopers found that the driver of a Chevrolet 2500 ran off the road at a curve through an embankment and struck two trees. Update: Pedestrian ID’d by Clay County Coroner in I-…
